1.name: Absorb
1.desc: A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

2.name: Acid
2.desc: The opposing Pokémon are attacked with a spray of harsh acid. This may also lower their Sp. Def stats.

3.name: Acid Armor
3.desc: The user alters its cellular structure to liquefy itself, sharply raising its Defense stat.

4.name: Aerial Ace
4.desc: The user confounds the target with speed, then slashes. This attack never misses.

5.name: Aeroblast
5.desc: A vortex of air is shot at the target to inflict damage. Critical hits land more easily.

6.name: Agility
6.desc: The user relaxes and lightens its body to move faster. This sharply raises the Speed stat.

7.name: Air Cutter
7.desc: The user launches razor-like wind to slash the opposing Pokémon. Critical hits land more easily.

8.name: Amnesia
8.desc: The user temporarily empties its mind to forget its concerns. This sharply raises the user's Sp. Def stat.

9.name: Ancient Power
9.desc: The user attacks with a prehistoric power. This may also raise all the user's stats at once.

10.name: Arm Thrust
10.desc: The user lets loose a flurry of open-palmed arm thrusts that hit two to five times in a row.

11.name: Aromatherapy
11.desc: The user releases a soothing scent that heals all status conditions affecting the users' party.

12.name: Assist
12.desc: The user hurriedly and randomly uses a move among those known by other Pokémon in the party.

13.name: Astonish
13.desc: The user attacks the target while shouting in a startling fashion. This may also make the target flinch.

14.name: Attract
14.desc: If it is the opposite gender of the user, the target becomes infatuated and less likely to attack.

15.name: Aurora Beam
15.desc: The target is hit with a rainbow-colored beam. This may also lower the target's Attack stat.

16.name: Barrage
16.desc: Round objects are hurled at the target to strike two to five times in a row.

17.name: Barrier
17.desc: The user throws up a sturdy wall that sharply raises its Defense stat.

18.name: Baton Pass
18.desc: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting and passes along any stat changes.

19.name: Beat Up
19.desc: The user gets all party Pokémon to attack the target. The more party Pokémon, the greater the number of attacks.

20.name: Belly Drum
20.desc: The user maximizes its Attack stat in exchange for HP equal to half its max HP.

21.name: Bide
21.desc: The user endures attacks for two turns, then strikes back to cause double the damage taken.

22.name: Bind
22.desc: Things such as long bodies or tentacles are used to bind and squeeze the target for four to five turns.

23.name: Bite
23.desc: The target is bitten with viciously sharp fangs. This may also make the target flinch.

24.name: Blaze Kick
24.desc: The user launches a kick that lands a critical hit more easily. This may also leave the target with a burn.

25.name: Blizzard
25.desc: A howling blizzard is summoned to strike opposing Pokémon. This may also leave the opposing Pokémon frozen.

26.name: 10000000 Volt Thunderbolt
26.desc: The user, Pikachu wearing a cap, powers up a jolt of electricity using its Z-Power and unleashes it. Critical hits land more easily.

27.name: Block
27.desc: The user blocks the target's way with arms spread wide to prevent escape.

28.name: Body Slam
28.desc: The user drops onto the target with its full body weight. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

29.name: Bone Club
29.desc: The user clubs the target with a bone. This may also make the target flinch.

30.name: Bone Rush
30.desc: The user strikes the target with a hard bone two to five times in a row.

31.name: Bonemerang
31.desc: The user throws the bone it holds. The bone loops to hit the target twice, coming and going.

32.name: Bounce
32.desc: The user bounces up high, then drops on the target on the second turn. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

33.name: Brick Break
33.desc: The user attacks with a swift chop. It can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.

34.name: Bubble
34.desc: A spray of countless bubbles is jetted at the opposing Pokémon. This may also lower their Speed stats.

35.name: Bubblebeam
35.desc: A spray of bubbles is forcefully ejected at the target. This may also lower its Speed stat.

36.name: Bulk Up
36.desc: The user tenses its muscles to bulk up its body, raising both its Attack and Defense stats.

37.name: Bullet Seed
37.desc: The user forcefully shoots seeds at the target two to five times in a row.

38.name: Calm Mind
38.desc: The user quietly focuses its mind and calms its spirit to raise its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

39.name: Camouflage
39.desc: The user's type is changed depending on its environment, such as at water's edge, in grass, or in a cave.

40.name: Charge
40.desc: The user boosts the power of the Electric move it uses on the next turn. This also raises the user's Sp. Def stat.

41.name: Charm
41.desc: The user gazes at the target rather charmingly, making it less wary. This harshly lowers its Attack stat.

42.name: Clamp
42.desc: The target is clamped and squeezed by the users' very thick and sturdy shell for four to five turns.

43.name: Comet Punch
43.desc: The target is hit with a flurry of punches that strike two to five times in a row.

44.name: Confuse Ray
44.desc: The target is exposed to a sinister ray that triggers confusion.

45.name: Confusion
45.desc: The target is hit by a weak telekinetic force. This may also confuse the target.

46.name: Constrict
46.desc: The target is hit by a weak telekinetic force. This may also confuse the target.

47.name: Acid Downpour
47.desc: The user creates a poisonous swamp using its Z-Power and sinks the target into it at full force. The power varies, depending on the original move.

48.name: Conversion
48.desc: The user changes its type to become the same type as the move at the top of the list of moves it knows.

49.name: Conversion 2
49.desc: The user changes its type to make itself resistant to the type of the attack the opponent used last.

50.name: Cosmic Power
50.desc: The user absorbs a mystical power from space to raise its Defense and Sp. Def stats.

51.name: Cotton Spore
51.desc: The user releases cotton-like spores that cling to the opposing Pokémon, which harshly lowers their Speed stats.

52.name: Counter
52.desc: A retaliation move that counters any physical attack, inflicting double the damage taken.

53.name: Covet
53.desc: The user endearingly approaches the target, then steals the target's held item.

54.name: Crabhammer
54.desc: The target is hammered with a large pincer. Critical hits land more easily.

55.name: Cross Chop
55.desc: The user delivers a double chop with its forearms crossed. Critical hits land more easily.

56.name: Crunch
56.desc: The user crunches up the target with sharp fangs. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

57.name: Crush Claw
57.desc: The user slashes the target with hard and sharp claws. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

58.name: Curse
58.desc: A move that works differently for the Ghost type than for all other types.

59.name: Defense Curl
59.desc: The user curls up to conceal weak spots and raise its Defense stat.

60.name: Destiny Bond
60.desc: When this move is used, if the user faints, the Pokémon that landed the knockout hit also faints.

61.name: Detect
61.desc: Enables the user to evade all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

62.name: Dig
62.desc: The user burrows, then attacks on the next turn. It can also be used to exit dungeons.

63.name: Disable
63.desc: For four turns, this move prevents the target from using the move it last used.

64.name: Dizzy Punch
64.desc: The target is hit with rhythmically launched punches. This may also leave the target confused.

65.name: Doom Desire
65.desc: Two turns after this move is used, the user blasts the target with a concentrated bundle of light.

66.name: All-Out Pummeling
66.desc: All-Out Pummeling inflicts damage. Its power and whether it is a special or physical move depends on the move it is based on.

67.name: Double Kick
67.desc: The target is quickly kicked twice in succession using both feet.

68.name: Ally Switch
68.desc: The user teleports using a strange power and switches places with one of its allies.

69.name: Double Team
69.desc: By moving rapidly, the user makes illusory copies of itself to raise its evasiveness.

70.name: Double-Edge
70.desc: A reckless, life-risking tackle. This also damages the user quite a lot.

71.name: Double Slap
71.desc: Repeatedly slaps the target 2 to 5 times.

72.name: Dragon Claw
72.desc: The user slashes the target with huge, sharp claws.

73.name: Dragon Dance
73.desc: The user vigorously performs a mystic, powerful dance that raises its Attack and Speed stats.

74.name: Dragon Rage
74.desc: This attack hits the target with a shock wave of pure rage. This attack always inflicts 40 HP damage.

75.name: Dragonbreath
75.desc: The user exhales a mighty gust that inflicts damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

76.name: Dream Eater
76.desc: The user eats the dreams of a sleeping target. It absorbs half the damage caused to heal its own HP.

77.name: Drill Peck
77.desc: A corkscrewing attack with a sharp beak acting as a drill.

78.name: Black Hole Eclipse
78.desc: The user gathers dark energy using its Z-Power and sucks the target into it. The power varies, depending on the original move.

79.name: Dynamic Punch
79.desc: The user punches the target with full, concentrated power. This confuses the target if it hits.

80.name: Earthquake
80.desc: The user sets off an earthquake that strikes every Pokémon around it.

81.name: Egg Bomb
81.desc: A large egg is hurled at the target with maximum force to inflict damage.

82.name: Ember
82.desc: The target is attacked with small flames. This may also leave the target with a burn.

83.name: Encore
83.desc: The user compels the target to keep using only the move it last used for three turns.

84.name: Endeavor
84.desc: An attack move that cuts down the target's HP to equal the user's HP.

85.name: Endure
85.desc: The user endures any attack with at least 1 HP. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

86.name: Eruption
86.desc: The user attacks opposing Pokémon with explosive fury. The lower the users' HP, the lower the move's power.

87.name: Explosion
87.desc: The user attacks everything around it by causing a tremendous explosion. The user faints upon using the move.

88.name: Extrasensory
88.desc: The user attacks with an odd, unseeable power. This may also make the target flinch.

89.name: Extreme Speed
89.desc: The user charges the target at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

90.name: Feint Attack
90.desc: The user approaches the target disarmingly, then throws a sucker punch. This attack never misses.

91.name: Fake Out
91.desc: An attack that hits first and makes the target flinch. It only works the first turn the user is in battle.

92.name: Fake Tears
92.desc: The user feigns crying to fluster the target, harshly lowering its Sp. Def stat.

93.name: False Swipe
93.desc: A restrained attack that prevents the target from fainting. The target is always left with at least 1 HP.

94.name: Feather Dance
94.desc: The user covers the target's body with a mass of down that harshly lowers its Attack stat.

95.name: Fire Blast
95.desc: The target is attacked with an intense blast of all-consuming fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.

96.name: Fire Punch
96.desc: The target is punched with a fiery fist. This may also leave the target with a burn.

97.name: Fire Spin
97.desc: The target becomes trapped within a fierce vortex of fire that rages for four to five turns.

98.name: Fissure
98.desc: The user opens up a fissure in the ground and drops the target in. The target faints instantly if this attack hits.

99.name: Flail
99.desc: The user flails aimlessly to attack. The less HP the user has, the greater the move's power.

100.name: Flame Wheel
100.desc: The user cloaks itself in fire and charges at the target. This may also leave the target with a burn.

101.name: Flamethrower
101.desc: The target is scorched with an intense blast of fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.

102.name: Flatter
102.desc: Flattery is used to confuse the target. However, this also raises the target's Sp. Atk stat.

103.name: Fly
103.desc: The user soars and then strikes its target on the next turn. This can also be used to fly to any familiar town.

104.name: Focus Energy
104.desc: The user takes a deep breath and focuses so that critical hits land more easily.

105.name: Focus Punch
105.desc: The user focuses its mind before launching a punch. This move fails if the user is hit before it is used.

106.name: Follow Me
106.desc: The user draws attention to itself, making all targets take aim only at the user.

107.name: Foresight
107.desc: Enables a Ghost-type target to be hit by Normal- and Fighting-type attacks. This also enables an evasive target to be hit.

108.name: Fury Attack
108.desc: The target is jabbed repeatedly with a horn or beak two to five times in a row.

109.name: Fury Cutter
109.desc: The target is slashed with scythes or claws. This attack becomes more powerful if it hits in succession.

110.name: Fury Swipes
110.desc: The target is raked with sharp claws or scythes quickly two to five times in a row.

111.name: Future Sight
111.desc: Two turns after this move is used, a hunk of psychic energy attacks the target.

112.name: Giga Drain
112.desc: A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

113.name: Glare
113.desc: The user intimidates the target with the pattern on its belly to cause paralysis.

114.name: Grass Whistle
114.desc: The user plays a pleasant melody that lulls the target into a deep sleep.

115.name: Growl
115.desc: The user growls in an endearing way, making opposing Pokémon less wary. This lowers their Attack stats.

116.name: Growth
116.desc: The user's body grows all at once, raising the Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

117.name: Grudge
117.desc: If the user faints, the user's grudge fully depletes the PP of the opponent's move that knocked it out.

118.name: Guillotine
118.desc: A vicious, tearing attack with big pincers. The target faints instantly if this attack hits.

119.name: Gust
119.desc: A gust of wind is whipped up by wings and launched at the target to inflict damage.

120.name: Hail
120.desc: The user summons a hailstorm lasting five turns. It damages all Pokémon except the Ice type.

121.name: Harden
121.desc: The user stiffens all the muscles in its body to raise its defense stat.

122.name: Haze
122.desc: The user creates a haze that eliminates every stat change among all the Pokémon engaged in battle.

123.name: Acrobatics
123.desc: The user nimbly strikes the target. If the user is not holding an item, this attack inflicts massive damage.

124.name: Headbutt
124.desc: The user sticks out its head and attacks by charging straight into the target. This may also make the target flinch.

125.name: Heal Bell
125.desc: The user makes a soothing bell chime to heal the status conditions of all the party Pokémon.

126.name: Heat Wave
126.desc: The user attacks by exhaling hot breath on the opposing Pokémon. This may also leave those Pokémon with a burn.

127.name: Helping Hand
127.desc: The user assists an ally by boosting the power of that ally's attack.

128.name: High Jump Kick
128.desc: The target is attacked with a knee kick from a jump. If it misses, the user is hurt instead.

129.name: Hidden Power
129.desc: A unique attack that varies in type depending on the Pokémon using it.

130.name: Horn Attack
130.desc: The target is jabbed with a sharply pointed horn to inflict damage.

131.name: Horn Drill
131.desc: The user stabs the target with a horn that rotates like a drill. The target faints instantly if this attack hits.

132.name: Howl
132.desc: The user howls loudly to raise its spirit, which raises its Attack stat.

133.name: Hydro Pump
133.desc: The target is blasted by a huge volume of water launched under great pressure.

134.name: Hyper Beam
134.desc: The target is attacked with a powerful beam. The user can't move on the next turn.

135.name: Hyper Fang
135.desc: The user bites hard on the target with its sharp front fangs. This may also make the target flinch.

136.name: Hyper Voice
136.desc: The user lets loose a horribly echoing shout with the power to inflict damage.

137.name: Hypnosis
137.desc: The users employs hypnotic suggestion to make the target fall into a deep sleep.

138.name: Ice Ball
138.desc: The user continually rolls into the target over five turns. It becomes stronger each time it hits.

139.name: Ice Beam
139.desc: The target is struck with an icy-cold beam of energy. This may also leave the target frozen.

140.name: Ice Punch
140.desc: The target is punched with an icy fist. This may also leave the target frozen.

141.name: Icicle Spear
141.desc: The user launches sharp icicles at the target two to five times in a row.

142.name: Icy Wind
142.desc: The user attacks with a gust of chilled air. This also lowers the opposing Pokémon's Speed stats.

143.name: Imprison
143.desc: If opposing Pokémon know any move also known by the user, they are prevented from using it.

144.name: Ingrain
144.desc: The user lays roots that restore its HP on every turn. Because it is rooted, it can't switch out.

145.name: Iron Defense
145.desc: The user hardens its body's surface like iron, sharply raising its Defense stat.

146.name: Iron Tail
146.desc: The target is slammed with a steel-hard tail. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

147.name: Jump Kick
147.desc: The user jumps up high, then strikes with a kick. If the kick misses, the user hurts itself.

148.name: Karate Chop
148.desc: The target is attacked with a sharp chop. Critical hits land more easily.

149.name: Kinesis
149.desc: The user distracts the target by bending a spoon. This lowers the target's accuracy.

150.name: Knock Off
150.desc: The user slaps down the target's held item, and that item can't be used in that battle. The move does more damage if the target has a held item.

151.name: Leaf Blade
151.desc: The user handles a sharp leaf like a sword and attacks by cutting its target. Critical hits land more easily.

152.name: Leech Life
152.desc: The user drains the target's blood. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

153.name: Leech Seed
153.desc: A seed is planted on the target. It steals some HP from the target every turn.

154.name: Leer
154.desc: The user gives opposing Pokémon an intimidating leer that lowers the Defense stat.

155.name: Lick
155.desc: The target is licked with a long tongue, causing damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

156.name: Light Screen
156.desc: A wonderous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from special attacks for five turns.

157.name: Aromatic Mist
157.desc: The user raises the Sp. Def stat of an ally Pokémon with a mysterious aroma.

158.name: Lock-On
158.desc: The user takes sure aim at the target. This ensures the next attack does not miss the target.

159.name: Lovely Kiss
159.desc: With a scary face, the user tries to force a kiss on the target. If it succeeds, the target falls asleep.

160.name: Low Kick
160.desc: A powerful low kick that makes the target fall over. The heavier the target, the greater the move's power.

161.name: Luster Purge
161.desc: The user lets loose a damaging burst of light. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

162.name: Mach Punch
162.desc: The user throws a punch at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

163.name: Magic Coat
163.desc: A barrier reflects back to the target moves like Leech Seed and moves that damage status.

164.name: Magical Leaf
164.desc: The user scatters curious leaves that chase the target. This attack never misses.

165.name: Magnitude
165.desc: The user attacks everything around it with a ground-shaking quake. Its power varies.

166.name: Mean Look
166.desc: The user pins the target with a dark, arresting look. The target becomes unable to flee.

167.name: Meditate
167.desc: The user meditates to awaken the power deep within its body and raise its Attack stat.

168.name: Mega Drain
168.desc: A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

169.name: Mega Kick
169.desc: The target is attacked by a kick launched with muscle-packed power.

170.name: Mega Punch
170.desc: The target is slugged by a punch thrown with muscle-packed power.

171.name: Megahorn
171.desc: Using its tough and impressive horn, the user rams into the target with no letup.

172.name: Memento
172.desc: The user faints when using this move. In return, this harshly lowers the target's Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

173.name: Metal Claw
173.desc: The target is raked with steel claws. This may also raise the users' Attack stat.

174.name: Metal Sound
174.desc: A horrible sound like scraping metal harshly lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.

175.name: Meteor Mash
175.desc: The target is hit with a hard punch fired like a meteor. This may also raise the user's Attack stat.

176.name: Metronome
176.desc: The user waggles a finger and stimulates its brain into randomly using nearly any move.

177.name: Milk Drink
177.desc: The user restores its own HP by up to half of its max HP. May also be used in the field to heal HP.

178.name: Mimic
178.desc: The user copies the target's last move. The move can be used during battle until the Pokémon is switched out.

179.name: Mind Reader
179.desc: The user senses the target's movements with its mind to ensure its next attack does not miss the target.

180.name: Minimize
180.desc: The user compresses its body to make itself look smaller, which sharply raises its evasiveness.

181.name: Mirror Coat
181.desc: A relitation move that counters any special attack, inflicting double the damage taken.

182.name: Mirror Move
182.desc: The user counters the target by mimicking the target's last move.

183.name: Mist
183.desc: The user cloaks itself and its allies in a white mist that prevents any of their stats from being lowered for five turns.

184.name: Mist Ball
184.desc: A mist-like flurry of down envelops and damages the target. This may also lower the target's Sp. Atk stat.

185.name: Moonlight
185.desc: The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.

186.name: Morning Sun
186.desc: The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.

187.name: Mud Shot
187.desc: The user attacks by hurling a blob of mud at the target. This may also lowers the target's Speed stat.

188.name: Mud-Slap
188.desc: The user hurls mud in the target's face to inflict damage and lower its accuracy.

189.name: Mud Sport
189.desc: The user launches a hard-packed mud ball to attack. This may also lower the target's accuracy.

190.name: Muddy Water
190.desc: The user attacks by shooting muddy water at the opposing Pokémon. This may also lower their accuracy.

191.name: Nature Power
191.desc: An attack that makes use of nature's power. Its effects vary depending on the user's environment.

192.name: Needle Arm
192.desc: The user attacks by wildly swinging its thorny arms. This may also make the target flinch.

193.name: Night Shade
193.desc: The user makes the target see a frightening mirage. It inflicts damage equal to the user's level.

194.name: Nightmare
194.desc: A sleeping target sees a nightmare that inflicts some damage every turn.

195.name: Octazooka
195.desc: The user attacks by spraying ink in the target's face or eyes. This may also lower the target's accuracy.

196.name: Odor Sleuth
196.desc: Enables a Ghost-type target to be hit by Normal- and Fighting-type attacks. This also enables an evasive target to be hit.

197.name: Outrage
197.desc: The user rampages and attacks for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.

198.name: Pain Split
198.desc: The user adds its HP to the target's HP, then equally shares the combined HP with the target.

199.name: Pay Day
199.desc: Numerous coins are hurled at the target to inflict damage.

200.name: Peck
200.desc: The target is jabbed with a sharply pointed beak or horn.

201.name: Perish Song
201.desc: Any Pokémon that hears this song faints in three turns, unless it switches out of battle.

202.name: Petal Dance
202.desc: The user attacks the target by scattering petals for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.

203.name: Pin Missile
203.desc: Sharp spikes are shot at the target in rapid succession. They hit two to five times in a row.

204.name: Poison Fang
204.desc: The user bites the target with toxic fangs. This may also leave the target badly poisoned.

205.name: Poison Gas
205.desc: A cloud of poison gas is sprayed in the face of opposing Pokémon. This may also poison those hit.

206.name: Poison Sting
206.desc: The user stabs the target with a poisonous stinger. This may also poison the target.

207.name: Poison Tail
207.desc: The user hits the target with its tail. This may also poison the target. Critical hits land more easily.

208.name: Poison Powder
208.desc: The user scatters a cloud of poisonous dust on the target. This may also poison the target.

209.name: Pound
209.desc: The target is physically pounded with a long tail, a foreleg, or the like.

210.name: Powder Snow
210.desc: The user attacks with a chilling gust of powdery snow. This may also freeze the opposing Pokémon.

211.name: Present
211.desc: The user attacks by giving the target a gift with a hidden trap. It restores HP sometimes, however.

212.name: Protect
212.desc: Enables the user to evade all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

213.name: Psybeam
213.desc: The target is attacked with a peculiar ray. This may also leave the target confused.

214.name: Psych Up
214.desc: The user hypnotizes itself into copying any stat change made by the target.

215.name: Psychic
215.desc: The target is hit by a strong telekinetic force. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

216.name: Psycho Boost
216.desc: The user attacks the target at full power. The attack's recoil harshly lowers the users' Sp. Atk stat.

217.name: Psywave
217.desc: The target is attacked with an odd psychic wave. The attack varies in intensity.

218.name: Pursuit
218.desc: An attack move that inflicts double damage if used on a target that is switching out of battle.

219.name: Quick Attack
219.desc: The user lunges at the target at a speed that makes it almost invisible. This move always goes first.

220.name: Rage
220.desc: As long as this move is in use, the power of rage raises the Attack stat each time the user is hit in battle.

221.name: Rain Dance
221.desc: The user summons a heavy rain that falls for five turns, powering up Water-type moves.

222.name: Rapid Spin
222.desc: A spin attack that can also eliminate such moves as Bind, Wrap, Leech Seed, and Spikes.

223.name: Razor Leaf
223.desc: Sharp-edged leaves are launched to slash at the opposing Pokémon. Critical hits land more easily.

224.name: Razor Wind
224.desc: A two-turn attack. Blades of wind hit opposing Pokémon on the second turn. Critical hits land more easily.

225.name: Recover
225.desc: Restoring its own cells, the user restores its own HP by half of its max HP.

226.name: Recycle
226.desc: The user recycles a held item that has been used in battle so it can be used again.

227.name: Reflect
227.desc: A wonderous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from physical attacks for five turns.

228.name: Refresh
228.desc: The user rests to cure itself of a poisoning, burn, or paralysis.

229.name: Rest
229.desc: The user goes to sleep for two turns. This fully restores the user's HP and heals any status conditions.

230.name: Revenge
230.desc: An attack move that inflicts double the damage if the user has been hurt by the opponent in the same turn.

231.name: Reversal
231.desc: An all-out attack that becomes more powerful the less HP the user has.

232.name: Roar
232.desc: The target is scared off, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

233.name: Rock Blast
233.desc: The user hurls hard rocks at the target. Two to five rocks are launched in a row.

234.name: Rock Slide
234.desc: Large boulders are hurled at the opposing Pokémon to inflict damage. This may also make the opposing Pokémon flinch.

235.name: Rock Throw
